item.dc:creator: @crackheadKD crackheadKD
item.description:
@crackheadKD wrote:

possible solutions (in order):

  1. its still working, at least it says so.
  2. if it isn’t working, try restarting your pc
  3. make sure you installed java and set your class paths
  4. if all of the above don’t work, try using my runserver

@echo off color 0a title Kids Destroy V1 java -Xmx512m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.08-ga-bin.jar server
To use this, right click your runserver, click edit, delete everything and paste this one inside to replace the old code; save.
